This	O
is	O
a	O
continuation	O
of	O
copending	O
application	O
Ser	O
.	O
No.	O
286	O
,	O
658	O
,	O
filed	O
on	O
Dec.	O
19	O
,	O
1988	O
,	O
now	O
abandoned	O
.	O

This	O
invention	O
relates	O
to	O
printers	O
and	O
ancillary	O
systems	O
for	O
use	O
therewith.Bar	O
codes	O
are	O
now	O
widely	O
used	O
for	O
ready	O
identification	O
and	O
tracking	O
of	O
products	O
,	O
samples	O
and	O
documents	O
.	O
For	O
example	O
,	O
they	O
are	O
finding	O
increasing	O
uses	O
in	O
medical	O
,	O
pharmaceutical	O
and	O
research	O
centres	O
as	O
well	O
as	O
in	O
retail	O
areas	O
.	O
Bar	O
codes	O
are	O
now	O
widely	O
used	O
at	O
goods-in	O
and	O
check-out	O
locations	O
associated	O
,	O
for	O
example	O
,	O
with	O
retail	O
trading	O
.	O
They	O
facilitate	O
the	O
use	O
of	O
fully	O
automatic	O
in-and-out	O
systems	O
and	O
,	O
in	O
some	O
instances	O
,	O
do	O
away	O
with	O
the	O
need	O
for	O
price	O
labels	O
on	O
the	O
products	O
.	O
Many	O
supermarkets	O
stock	O
25	O
,	O
000	O
to	O
30	O
,	O
000	O
items	O
for	O
sale	O
,	O
however	O
,	O
and	O
do	O
not	O
have	O
sufficient	O
shelf	O
space	O
to	O
allocate	O
all	O
of	O
these	O
items	O
to	O
a	O
particular	O
position	O
;	O
as	O
a	O
result	O
,	O
even	O
if	O
there	O
is	O
a	O
bar	O
code	O
on	O
such	O
products	O
,	O
there	O
is	O
still	O
a	O
need	O
for	O
price	O
marking	O
.	O
Nevertheless	O
,	O
the	O
use	O
of	O
a	O
bar	O
code	O
scanning	O
system	O
to	O
identify	O
the	O
goods	O
may	O
reduce	O
labour	O
requirements	O
significantly	O
and	O
thus	O
produce	O
considerable	O
savings	O
.	O
In	O
supermarkets	O
,	O
typically	O
95	O
-	O
96	O
%	O
of	O
food	O
items	O
going	O
through	O
the	O
check-out	O
have	O
a	O
bar	O
code	O
already	O
printed	O
at	O
source	O
by	O
the	O
manufacturer	O
.	O
For	O
non-food	O
items	O
,	O
the	O
number	O
of	O
products	O
bar	O
coded	O
at	O
source	O
is	O
typically	O
80	O
-	O
85	O
%	O
of	O
those	O
going	O
through	O
the	O
check-out.In	O
order	O
to	O
apply	O
price	O
labels	O
to	O
items	O
already	O
carrying	O
a	O
bar	O
code	O
,	O
and	O
to	O
add	O
a	O
bar	O
code	O
to	O
those	O
products	O
which	O
are	O
not	O
coded	O
at	O
source	O
,	O
it	O
is	O
common	O
for	O
a	O
retail	O
outlet	O
to	O
use	O
one	O
or	O
more	O
label	O
printers	O
.	O
These	O
may	O
be	O
hand-held	O
,	O
portable	O
or	O
fixed	O
in	O
position	O
.	O
Typically	O
,	O
three	O
stationary	O
printers	O
may	O
be	O
used	O
by	O
up	O
to	O
ten	O
people	O
.	O
Strips	O
of	O
labels	O
will	O
be	O
printed	O
and	O
taken	O
to	O
the	O
product	O
and	O
either	O
applied	O
by	O
hand	O
or	O
with	O
a	O
dispenser	O
.	O
Some	O
retailers	O
consider	O
that	O
it	O
is	O
more	O
economical	O
for	O
each	O
operative	O
to	O
have	O
his	O
own	O
hand-held	O
bar	O
code	O
label	O
printer	O
.	O
If	O
a	O
national	O
bar	O
code	O
has	O
been	O
allocated	O
to	O
a	O
given	O
product	O
,	O
this	O
will	O
normally	O
be	O
used	O
by	O
the	O
retailer	O
if	O
no	O
manufacturer	O
's	O
bar	O
code	O
is	O
present	O
.	O
For	O
products	O
where	O
no	O
such	O
national	O
bar	O
code	O
has	O
been	O
allocated	O
,	O
it	O
is	O
up	O
to	O
the	O
retailer	O
to	O
decide	O
on	O
his	O
own	O
bar	O
code	O
number	O
.	O
Typically	O
,	O
this	O
number	O
might	O
be	O
based	O
on	O
the	O
numbering	O
system	O
used	O
by	O
the	O
retailer	O
before	O
the	O
introduction	O
of	O
bar	O
code	O
scanning	O
to	O
his	O
store	O
.	O
In	O
practice	O
,	O
the	O
person	O
generating	O
bar	O
codes	O
with	O
a	O
printer	O
will	O
have	O
with	O
him	O
source	O
material	O
which	O
indicates	O
the	O
nature	O
of	O
the	O
bar	O
code	O
for	O
each	O
product	O
where	O
a	O
label	O
is	O
required	O
.	O
In	O
medical	O
application	O
,	O
bar	O
codes	O
are	O
useful	O
in	O
patient	O
identification	O
,	O
specimen	O
collection	O
and	O
distribution	O
,	O
pharmaceuticals	O
distribution	O
,	O
document	O
tracking	O
,	O
and	O
management	O
applications	O
such	O
as	O
accounting	O
,	O
time	O
recording/allocating	O
,	O
supplies	O
management	O
,	O
and	O
tracking	O
of	O
personnel	O
and	O
documents.Hand-held	O
labelling	O
machines	O
typically	O
comprise	O
a	O
housing	O
which	O
is	O
supported	O
by	O
a	O
handle	O
.	O
Such	O
a	O
machine	O
may	O
include	O
a	O
label	O
supply	O
roll	O
within	O
said	O
housing	O
;	O
a	O
printing	O
unit	O
;	O
and	O
a	O
keyboard	O
for	O
inputting	O
data	O
.	O
When	O
such	O
a	O
machine	O
is	O
used	O
to	O
print	O
bar	O
code	O
labels	O
,	O
an	O
operative	O
will	O
input	O
the	O
bar	O
code	O
number	O
via	O
the	O
keyboard	O
,	O
and	O
then	O
activates	O
a	O
label	O
feed	O
mechanism	O
and	O
the	O
printing	O
unit	O
to	O
apply	O
the	O
requested	O
bar	O
code	O
to	O
one	O
of	O
the	O
labels	O
on	O
the	O
supply	O
roll	O
.	O
After	O
the	O
bar	O
code	O
has	O
been	O
printed	O
,	O
the	O
label	O
feed	O
mechanism	O
moves	O
the	O
supply	O
roll	O
so	O
that	O
the	O
printed	O
label	O
is	O
accessible	O
for	O
application	O
to	O
the	O
appropriate	O
goods	O
item	O
.	O
The	O
keyboard	O
of	O
such	O
a	O
printer	O
can	O
constitute	O
a	O
relatively	O
